SWNS/BoF Herring MSE MP Testing Results

2024-03-22

Summary of Results

Objectives

MSE Objectives

Conservation Objective
1. Maintain the stock above the LRP with at least 75% probability in each year in years 10-15 of the projection period for each OM in the reference set.

Stakeholder Objectives
2. Maintain SSB above a target biomass in the long-term
3. Maximize short-term yield
4. Maximize long-term yield
5. Minimize variability in catch
6. Limit the removal of small fish

Performance Metrics

Minimum Performance Standard for the Conservation Objective

  1. P(model estimated SSB > model estimated SSB2005-2010) > 0.75 in each year in years 10-15 of the projection period for each OM in the reference set.

    Model estimated SSB2005-2010 = the mean SSB from 2005-2010

    The minimum performance standard is used to eliminate MPs from further consideration

Performance Metrics

Objective Metric Timeframe
    1. Maintain SSB above a target biomass in the long-term
P(three-yr moving average acoustic index >425kt) Years 16-25
    1. Maintain SSB above a target biomass in the long term
P(three-yr moving average acoustic index >500kt) Years 16-25
  1. Maximize short-term yield
Average Yield Years 4-8
  1. Maximize long-term yield
Average Yield Years 6-25
  1. Minimize variability in catch
Average inter-annual variability in yield Years 4-25
  1. Limit the removal of small fish
% Small Fish by number (<23 cm) Years 4-15

These performance metrics are used to rank the performance of MPs and are not used to eliminate MPs from consideration. Note that 425kt represents a potential target biomass used for ranking the performance of MPs. A target biomass of 500kt is also used to show that the relative ranking of the performance of MPs is the same regardless of the magnitude of the target biomass

OMs

Reference Set

An initial set of OMs was defined as a full factorial cross of the levels of 4 axes of uncertainty:

  • Natural Mortality Rate:
    • 1: M = 0.35
    • 2: M = 0.49 (Age 0-2) and 0.26 (Age 3+)
    • 3: M = 0.72 (Age 0-2) and 0.45 (Age 3+)
  • Future Growth:
    • A: status quo: mean of last 3 years
    • B: temporal trend: extrapolation of regression of weight at age vs.year
    • Binv: reverse temporal trend: reversal of the magnitude change in weight-at-age in B
  • Steepness:
    • H: h = 0.95
    • L: h = 0.65
  • Weir catch and size composition data:
    • -: exclude weir fleet
    • +: include weir fleet

Future recruitment is based on the mean recruitment deviations from 1990-2017.


The reference set of OMs was defined to include the 12 OMs with natural mortality rate level 1: M = 0.35

A set of OMs was defined from these uncertainties:

  • Natural Mortality Rate:
    • 1: M = 0.35

    • B: temporal trend: extrapolation of regression of weight at age vs.year

    • -: exclude weir fleet
    • +: include weir fleet
  • Future recruitment
    • 90-17: future recruitment based on mean recruitment deviations from 1990-2017 (from reference set assumption)
    • 68-17: future recruitment based on mean recruitment deviations from 1968-2017
    • 90%: future recruitment based on the lower 90% of historical recruitment deviations

Tmin

Tmin is defined as the time to rebuild above a rebuilding target when no fishing occurs. For SWNS/BoF, the rebuilding target is objective 1: P(Model estimated SSB > Model estimated SSB2005-2010) > 0.75 in each year in years 10-15 of the projection period for each OM in the reference set.

Notes

Tmin is calculated for each OM individually.
Since fishing occurred in 2021, 2022, and 2023 Tmin was calculated using projection year 4 (2024) as the first year of rebuilding.

Table of Results by MP

Median value or probability for the most pessimistic OM, median performing OM, and most optimistic OM for each metric
minP(SSB>SSB0510) = minimum annual probability of model estimated SSB being above the mean model estimated SSB from 2005-2010 in projection years 10-15

P(>425) = Probability 3-yr moving average index > 425kt

P(>500) = Probability 3-yr moving average index > 500kt

STY = Short term (4-8 year) yield (kt)

LTY = Long term (9-25 year) yield (kt)

AAVY = average annual variability in yield (%)

% < 23cm = % of catch < 23 cm by number over years 1-15
